<h3 id="vendor-invoice-line-distributions" sourcefile="articles/finance/accounts-payable/mobile-invoice-approvals.md" sourcestartlinenumber="342">Vendor invoice line distributions</h3>
<p sourcefile="articles/finance/accounts-payable/mobile-invoice-approvals.md" sourcestartlinenumber="344">The requirements for this scenario confirm that there will be only line-level distributions, and that an invoice will always have only one line. Because this scenario is simple, the user experience on the mobile device must also be simple enough that the user doesn’t have to drill down several levels to view the distributions. Vendor invoices include the option of showing all distributions from the invoice header. This experience is what we need for the mobile scenario. Therefore, we will use the <strong sourcefile="articles/finance/accounts-payable/mobile-invoice-approvals.md" sourcestartlinenumber="344">VendMobileInvoiceAllDistributionTree</strong> page to design this part of the mobile scenario.</p>
